activities:
Votenet uses Personally Identifiable Information to maintain client points of contact, and to process payment from clients.
Votenet also receives:

(a)  names, addresses, telephone numbers, email addresses, membership status/ID or other identifying numbers, passwords or other personal codes or information which can be used in combination to collect information of a personal nature relating to voting participants;
 
(b)  date and time on which the computer of a voting participant accessed the Votenet system and name of the ballot so accessed, and the website the voting participant's browser left to come to the Votenet site;
 
(c)  the voting participant's computer’s IP address, his/her member number or other personal information such as a birth date or email address to serve as a username or password; and
 
(d)  information about how a voting participant voted.
